com.foreach.across.modules.entity.registry.properties

Class EntityPropertySelector

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.foreach.across.modules.entity.registry.properties.EntityPropertySelector

  • public class EntityPropertySelector
extends Object
    Selection predicate for a number of properties. Allows incremental building of the selector. Property names can be added with the following options:
    • .: keep all configured rules
    • *: represents all properties returned when applying the default filter
    • **: represents all properties registered, ignoring any default filter
    • :readable: all readable properties
    • :writable: all writable properties
    • propertyName: exactly that property
    • ~propertyName: not that property
    Selecting properties happens in 3 stages:
    1. selecting all properties using the include selectors
    2. applying the Predicate to those properties if there is one
    3. excluding all explicitly excluded properties
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme
    See Also:
    EntityPropertySelector.Builder

      • combine

        public EntityPropertySelector combine(EntityPropertySelector other)
        Combines the current selector with another selector. If the other selector contains the CONFIGURED property, then the result will be a merged selector. In any other case, the other selector will in fact replace the current selector.
        Parameters:
        other - selector to combine with
        Returns:
        other selector or a union of current and other selector if the other contains the CONFIGURED rule
